# Voice Guidance for InsightPress

This file helps InsightPress match your writing tone (optional).

Add 5-10 example posts you've written in your preferred style.
The system will analyze sentence length and tone heuristically.

## Example Posts

Kubernetes 1.30 changes how autoscaling works under load. Worth understanding the trade-offs before adopting.

New Rust RFC addresses memory safety in async contexts. This matters for anyone building concurrent systems at scale.

Security researchers found privilege escalation in common container runtime. Patch urgently if you're running this in production.

AWS announced managed Prometheus at half the cost. Could reduce operational overhead for observability teams.

OpenAI released structured output mode for GPT-4. This is the kind of guardrail teams need to stop unvetted LLM usage creeping into prod.

## Guidelines

- Keep sentences short and direct (aim for 15-25 words)
- Lead with what changed, follow with why it matters
- Avoid emojis, clickbait, and rhetorical questions
- Focus on practitioner implications (cost, risk, workflow)
- Use concrete terms over abstract hype
